main event: Bright lights were observed moving in a zig-zag pattern over Tyndall AFB, Florida, from December 16 to 20, 1960.
interesting points: The lights were seen between 1800-2000 hours and appeared to be moving at high altitudes of 10,000-12,000 feet., Witnesses reported that the object seemed to stop and move in spurts during the observation., The object appeared similar to a bright star, but was larger and brighter than any known object in the sky., The sighting was made by military personnel at the base, including MSGT G. Traynor., The object had been observed multiple times across different nights, suggesting a recurring phenomenon.
sighted object: a bright light moving in a zig-zag pattern
